ehydes, but is distinct from EC [1.2.3.1](/EC/1.2.3.1).\n-   Under some conditions the product is mainly superoxide rather than peroxide: R-H + H2O + 2 O2 = ROH + 2 O2(.-) + 2 H(+).\n-   The mammallian enzyme predominantly exists as an NAD-dependent dehydrogenase (EC [1.17.1.4](/EC/1.17.1.4)).\n-   During purification the enzyme is largely converted to the O2-dependent xanthine oxidase form (EC [1.17.3.2](/EC/1.17.3.2)).\n-   The conversion can be triggered by several mechanisms, including the oxidation of cysteine thiols to form disulfide bonds (which can be catalyzed by EC [1.8.4.7](/EC/1.8.4.7) in the presence of glutathione disulfide) or limited proteolysis, which results in irreversible conversion.\n-   The conversion can also occur in vivo.\n-   Formerly EC 1.1.3.22 and EC [1.2.3.2](/EC/1.2.3.2).\n\nCross-references\n\nRhea expert-curated reactions\n\n[1.17.3.2](https://www.rhea-db.org/rhea?query=ec%3A1.17.3.2)\n\nExplorEnz\n\n[1.17.3.2](http://www.enzyme-database.org/query.php?ec=1.17.3.2)\n\nIUBMB Enzyme Nomenclature\n\n[1.17.3.2](https://www.qmul.ac.uk/sbcs/iubmb/enzyme/EC1/17/3/2.html)\n\nUniProtKB/Swiss-Prot\n\n[P80457](https://www.uniprot.org/uniprot/P80457), XDH\\_BOVIN\n\n[P47990](https://www.uniprot.org/uniprot/P47990), XDH\\_CHICK\n\n[Q9MYW6](https://www.uniprot.org/uniprot/Q9MYW6), XDH\\_FELCA\n\n[P47989](https://www.uniprot.org/uniprot/P47989), XDH\\_HUMAN\n\n[Q00519](https://www.uniprot.org/uniprot/Q00519), XDH\\_MOUSE\n\n[P22985](https://www.uniprot.org/uniprot/P22985), XDH\\_RAT\n\nBRENDA\n\n[1.17.3.2](http://www.brenda-enzymes.org/enzyme.php?ecno=1.17.3.2)\n\nMetaCyc\n\n[1.17.3.2](https://biocyc.org/META/NEW-IMAGE?type=EC-NUMBER&object=EC-1.17.3.2)\n\nKEGG Ligand Database for Enzyme Nomenclature\n\n[1.17.3.2](http://www.genome.ad.jp/dbget-bin/www_bget?ec:1.17.3.2)\n\nEC2PDB\n\n[1.17.3.2](https://www.ebi.ac.uk/thornton-srv/databases/cgi-bin/enzymes/GetPage.pl?ec_number=1.17.3.2)\n\nMEDLINE\n\n[Find literature relating to 1.17.3.2](https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/entrez/query.fcgi?cmd=PureSearch&db=PubMed&details_term=1.17.3.2[EC/RN%20Number])\n\n  \n[View entry in original ENZYME format](/cgi-bin/enzyme/get-enzyme-entry?1.17.3.2)  \n[View entry in raw text format (no links)](/EC/1.17.3.2.txt)  \n\n[All UniProtKB/Swiss-Prot entries referenced in this entry](https://www.uniprot.org/uniprotkb?query=\\(ec:1.17.3.2\\)%20AND%20\\(reviewed:true\\)), with possibility to download in different formats, align etc.\n\nAll [ENZYME](/EC/1.17.3.-) / [UniProtKB/Swiss-Prot](https://www.uniprot.org/uniprotkb?query=\\(ec:1.17.3.-\\)%20AND%20\\(reviewed:true\\)) entries corresponding to 1.17.3.-  \nAll [ENZYME](/EC/1.17.-.-) / [UniProtKB/Swiss-Prot](https://www.uniprot.org/uniprotkb?query=\\(ec:1.17.-.-\\)%20AND%20\\(reviewed:true\\)) entries corresponding to 1.17.-.-  \nAll [ENZYME](/EC/1.-.-.-) / [UniProtKB/Swiss-Prot](https://www.uniprot.org/uniprotkb?query=\\(ec:1.-.-.-\\)%20AND%20\\(reviewed:true\\)) entries corresponding to 1.-.-.-  \n\n![SIB logo](/images/sib_images/sib-mark.svg)\n\n[Expasy](https://www.expasy.org) is operated by the [SIB Swiss Institute of Bioinformatics](https://sib.swiss)  \n[Terms of Use](https://www.expasy.org/terms-of-use) | [Privacy policy](https://www.sib.swiss/privacy-policy)\n\n[Back to the top](#top)","metadata":{"truncated":false},"title":"https://enzyme.expasy.org/EC/1.17.3.2 (text/html; charset=UTF-8)","time":{"start":1778431533901,"end":1778431536137}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0f5755a5ac35cdb1016a00b62dc5ec81929758a19e1e1ce64b"}},"id":"prt_e12c7a34b001gyi5WyJfbQfXWe","sessionID":"ses_1ed3f6926ffeBLriFMTumDj8z2","messageID":"msg_e12c782a1001TL7AUg7xWhfHIL"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778431536193,"sessionID":"ses_1ed3f6926ffeBLriFMTumDj8z2","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"webfetch","callID":"call_69Vs8KkAxcjMI3SO7cLepd7I","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"url":"https://enzyme.expasy.org/EC/1.14.14.24","format":"markdown","timeout":120},"output":"         ENZYME - 1.14.14.24 vitamin D 25-hydroxylase\n\n![Expasy logo](/images/expasy_logos/Expasy_logo_base_addon.svg)\n\n#### [ENZYME](https://enzyme.expasy.org)\n\n-   ![home](/images/icons/home.svg) [Home](/index.html)\n-   ![tool](/images/icons/tool.svg) [Browse](/cgi-bin/enzyme/enzyme-search-cl?1)\n    -   [by classes](/cgi-bin/enzyme/enzyme-search-cl?1)\n    -   [by subclasses](/cgi-bin/enzyme/enzyme-search-cl?2)\n    -   [by subsubclasses](/cgi-bin/enzyme/enzyme-search-cl?3)\n-   ![browse](/images/icons/browse.svg) [Search](/enzyme-search-ec.html)\n    -   [by EC number](/enzyme-search-ec.html)\n    -   [by name](/enzyme-byname.html)\n    -   [by chemical compound](/enzyme-bycompound.html)\n    -   [by comment](/enzyme-bycomment.html)\n-   ![documents](/images/icons/documents.svg) [Documentation](https://ftp.expasy.org/databases/enzyme/)\n    -   [User Manual](https://ftp.expasy.org/databases/enzyme/enzuser.txt)\n    -   [Access to ENZYME](https://ftp.expasy.org/databases/enzyme/enzyme.get)\n-   ![download](/images/icons/download.svg) [Downloads](https://ftp.expasy.org/databases/enzyme/)\n-   ![contact](/images/icons/contact.svg) [Contact](/contact)\n\n# ENZYME entry: EC 1.14.14.24\n\n[PURL](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Persistent_uniform_resource_locator): [https://purl.expasy.org/enzyme/EC/1.14.14.24](https://purl.expasy.org/enzyme/EC/1.14.14.24)\n\nAccepted Name\n\n**vitamin D 25-hydroxylase**\n\nAlternative Name(s)\n\n**CYP2R1**\n\n**vitamin D2 25-hydroxylase**\n\n**vitamin D3 25-hydroxylase**\n\nReaction catalysed\n\ncalciol + reduced \\[NADPH--hemoprotein reductase\\] + O2 = calcidiol + oxidized \\[NADPH--hemoprotein reductase\\] + H2O + H(+)\n\nComment(s)\n\n-   A microsomal enzyme isolated from human and mouse liver that bioactivates vitamin D3.\n-   While multiple isoforms (CYP27A1, CYP2J2/3, CYP3A4, CYP2D25 and CYP2C11) are able to catalyze the reaction in vitro, only CYP2R1 is thought to catalyze the reaction in humans in vivo.\n-   The direct electron donor to the enzyme is EC [1.6.2.4](/EC/1.6.2.4).\n-   Formerly EC 1.14.13.159.\n\nCross-references\n\nRhea expert-curated reactions\n\n[1.14.14.24](https://www.rhea-db.org/rhea?query=ec%3A1.14.14.24)\n\nExplorEnz\n\n[1.14.14.24](http://www.enzyme-database.org/query.php?ec=1.14.14.24)\n\nIUBMB Enzyme Nomenclature\n\n[1.14.14.24](https://www.qmul.ac.uk/sbcs/iubmb/enzyme/EC1/14/14/24.html)\n\nUniProtKB/Swiss-Prot\n\n[O46658](https://www.uniprot.org/uniprot/O46658), CP2DP\\_PIG\n\n[Q6VVX0](https://www.uniprot.org/uniprot/Q6VVX0), CP2R1\\_HUMAN\n\n[Q6VVW9](https://www.uniprot.org/uniprot/Q6VVW9), CP2R1\\_MOUSE\n\nBRENDA\n\n[1.14.14.24](http://www.brenda-enzymes.org/enzyme.php?ecno=1.14.14.24)\n\nMetaCyc\n\n[1.14.14.24](https://biocyc.org/META/NEW-IMAGE?type=EC-NUMBER&object=EC-1.14.14.24)\n\nKEGG Ligand Database for Enzyme Nomenclature\n\n[1.14.14.24](http://www.genome.ad.jp/dbget-bin/www_bget?ec:1.14.14.24)\n\nEC2PDB\n\n[1.14.14.24](https://www.ebi.ac.uk/thornton-srv/databases/cgi-bin/enzymes/GetPage.pl?ec_number=1.14.14.24)\n\nMEDLINE\n\n[Find literature relating to 1.14.14.24](https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/entrez/query.fcgi?cmd=PureSearch&db=PubMed&details_term=1.14.14.24[EC/RN%20Number])\n\n  \n[View entry in original ENZYME format](/cgi-bin/enzyme/get-enzyme-entry?1.14.14.24)  \n[View entry in raw text format (no links)](/EC/1.14.14.24.txt)  \n\n[All UniProtKB/Swiss-Prot entries referenced in this entry](https://www.uniprot.org/uniprotkb?query=\\(ec:1.14.14.24\\)%20AND%20\\(reviewed:true\\)), with possibility to download in different formats, align etc.\n\nAll [ENZYME](/EC/1.14.14.-) / [UniProtKB/Swiss-Prot](https://www.uniprot.org/uniprotkb?query=\\(ec:1.14.14