ADPH + H(+)\n\nComment(s)\n\n-   The enzyme participates in an alternative pathway for biosynthesis of (R)-pantothenate (vitamin B5).\n-   This entry covers enzymes whose stereo specificity for NADP(+) is not known (cf. EC [1.1.1.168](/EC/1.1.1.168) and EC [1.1.1.214](/EC/1.1.1.214)).\n\nCross-references\n\nRhea expert-curated reactions\n\n[1.1.1.358](https://www.rhea-db.org/rhea?query=ec%3A1.1.1.358)\n\nExplorEnz\n\n[1.1.1.358](http://www.enzyme-database.org/query.php?ec=1.1.1.358)\n\nIUBMB Enzyme Nomenclature\n\n[1.1.1.358](https://www.qmul.ac.uk/sbcs/iubmb/enzyme/EC1/1/1/358.html)\n\nUniProtKB/Swiss-Prot\n\n[Q76L37](https://www.uniprot.org/uniprot/Q76L37), CPRC1\\_CANPA\n\n[Q76L36](https://www.uniprot.org/uniprot/Q76L36), CPRC2\\_CANPA\n\nBRENDA\n\n[1.1.1.358](http://www.brenda-enzymes.org/enzyme.php?ecno=1.1.1.358)\n\nMetaCyc\n\n[1.1.1.358](https://biocyc.org/META/NEW-IMAGE?type=EC-NUMBER&object=EC-1.1.1.358)\n\nKEGG Ligand Database for Enzyme Nomenclature\n\n[1.1.1.358](http://www.genome.ad.jp/dbget-bin/www_bget?ec:1.1.1.358)\n\nEC2PDB\n\n[1.1.1.358](https://www.ebi.ac.uk/thornton-srv/databases/cgi-bin/enzymes/GetPage.pl?ec_number=1.1.1.358)\n\nMEDLINE\n\n[Find literature relating to 1.1.1.358](https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/entrez/query.fcgi?cmd=PureSearch&db=PubMed&details_term=1.1.1.358[EC/RN%20Number])\n\n  \n[View entry in original ENZYME format](/cgi-bin/enzyme/get-enzyme-entry?1.1.1.358)  \n[View entry in raw text format (no links)](/EC/1.1.1.358.txt)  \n\n[All UniProtKB/Swiss-Prot entries referenced in this entry](https://www.uniprot.org/uniprotkb?query=\\(ec:1.1.1.358\\)%20AND%20\\(reviewed:true\\)), with possibility to download in different formats, align etc.\n\nAll [ENZYME](/EC/1.1.1.-) / [UniProtKB/Swiss-Prot](https://www.uniprot.org/uniprotkb?query=\\(ec:1.1.1.-\\)%20AND%20\\(reviewed:true\\)) entries corresponding to 1.1.1.-  \nAll [ENZYME](/EC/1.1.-.-) / [UniProtKB/Swiss-Prot](https://www.uniprot.org/uniprotkb?query=\\(ec:1.1.-.-\\)%20AND%20\\(rev